# Workflow

## Before implementing

1. If any decision has multiple valid options, ask arbitrage questions first
2. If everything is obvious and unambiguous, proceed directly — no need to ask
3. When questions were asked, summarize choices and get confirmation before writing

## After implementing

1. Always re-read what was created
2. Verify all project rules have been respected (structure, naming, style, etc.)
3. Present review findings: what's good, what's potentially wrong or inconsistent
4. If issues are found, propose fixes and ask for the user's decision
5. **If corrections were applied, re-read and review again** — repeat until no more issues are found
6. Only move on when the user confirms the result is satisfactory
